data.title: Pair of pop-up vaccine clinics coming to high schools in Brampton and Mississauga on Thursday
data.meta_description: The Region of Peel is operating a pair of pop-up vaccination clinics in Brampton and Mississauga
data.text:
The Region of Peel is operating a pair of pop-up vaccination clinics in Brampton and Mississauga.

On Thursday, clinics will be held at Cardinal Ambrozic Catholic Secondary School, located at 10 Castle Oaks Crossing in Brampton; and École secondaire catholique Sainte-Famille, located at 1780 Meadowvale Boulevard in Mississauga.

Both clinics will run from 5 to 7:30 p.m. Walk-ins are welcome, and appointments can be made through the Region’s online booking portal.

The clinic will be serving residents who are ages 12 and older.
